#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.247"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.247:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.247:0.2"
msgid "19. Āsīvisavagga"
msgstr "19. The Simile of the Vipers"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 247. Chappāṇakopamasutta → chappāṇakasuttaṃ (bj) | chapāṇa (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.247:0.3"
msgid "247. Chappāṇakopamasutta"
msgstr "247. The Simile of Six Animals"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.247:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso arugatto pakkagatto saravanaṃ paviseyya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose a person with wounded and festering limbs was to enter "
"a thicket of thorny reeds."

#. VAR: sarapattāni ca gattāni → sarapattāni pakkagattāni (s1-3, km) | arupakkāni gattāni (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.247:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa kusakaṇṭakā ceva pāde vijjheyyuṃ, sarapattāni ca gattāni vilekheyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"The kusa thorns would pierce their feet, and the reed leaves would scratch "
"their limbs."

msgctxt "sn35.247:1.3"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, puriso bhiyyoso mattāya tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvediyetha."
msgstr ""
"And that would cause that person to experience even more pain and distress."

msgctxt "sn35.247:1.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu gāmagato vā araññagato vā labhati "
"vattāraṃ:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, some mendicant goes to a village or a wilderness and gets "
"scolded:"

#. VAR: ayañca so → ayañca kho (pts1, mr) | ayaṃ so (?)
msgctxt "sn35.247:1.5"
msgid "‘ayañca so āyasmā evaṃkārī evaṃsamācāro asucigāmakaṇṭako’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This venerable, acting like this, behaving like this, is a filthy village "
"thorn.’"

msgctxt "sn35.247:1.6"
msgid "Taṃ kaṇṭakoti iti viditvā saṃvaro ca asaṃvaro ca veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"Understanding that they’re a thorn, they should understand restraint and "
"lack of restraint."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.247:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, asaṃvaro hoti?"
msgstr "And how is someone unrestrained?"

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe adhimuccati, "
"appiyarūpe rūpe byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati parittacetaso. "
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with their eyes. If it’s pleasant they "
"hold on to it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with "
"mindfulness of the body unestablished and their heart restricted. "

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.3"
msgid ""
"Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, yatthassa te "
"uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom "
"where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left "
"over."

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.8"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme adhimuccati, appiyarūpe dhamme "
"byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati parittacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, if it’s pleasant they hold on to "
"it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of "
"the body unestablished and a limited heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.247:2.9"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, yatthassa te "
"uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom "
"where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left "
"over."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.199"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.247:3.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso chappāṇake gahetvā nānāvisaye nānāgocare "
"daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to catch six animals, with diverse territories and "
"feeding grounds, and tie them up with a strong rope."

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.2"
msgid "Ahiṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "They’d catch a snake,"

#. VAR: Susumāraṃ → suṃsumāraṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.247:3.3"
msgid "Susumāraṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "a crocodile,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.4"
msgid "Pakkhiṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "a bird,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.5"
msgid "Kukkuraṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "a dog,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.6"
msgid "Siṅgālaṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "a jackal,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.7"
msgid "Makkaṭaṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "and a monkey,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.8"
msgid "Daḷhāya rajjuyā bandhitvā majjhe gaṇṭhiṃ karitvā ossajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"tie each up with a strong rope, then tie a knot in the middle and let them "
"loose."

#. VAR: āviñcheyyuṃ → āviñjeyyuṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.247:3.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, te, bhikkhave, chappāṇakā nānāvisayā nānāgocarā sakaṃ sakaṃ "
"gocaravisayaṃ āviñcheyyuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Then those six animals with diverse domains and territories would each pull "
"towards their own domain and territory."

#. VAR: sīvathikaṃ → sivathikaṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.247:3.10"
msgid ""
"ahi āviñcheyya ‘vammikaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti, susumāro āviñcheyya ‘udakaṃ "
"pavekkhāmī’ti, pakkhī āviñcheyya ‘ākāsaṃ ḍessāmī’ti, kukkuro āviñcheyya ‘"
"gāmaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti, siṅgālo āviñcheyya ‘sīvathikaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti, makkaṭo "
"āviñcheyya ‘vanaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"The snake would pull one way, thinking ‘I’m going into an anthill!’ The "
"crocodile would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the water!’ The "
"bird would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m flying into the sky!’ The dog "
"would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the village!’ The jackal "
"would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the charnel ground!’ The "
"monkey would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the jungle!’"

#. VAR: pāṇakānaṃ → pāṇako (bj) | pāṇakā (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn35.247:3.11"
msgid ""
"Yadā kho te, bhikkhave, chappāṇakā jhattā assu kilantā, atha kho yo nesaṃ "
"pāṇakānaṃ balavataro assa tassa te anuvatteyyuṃ, anuvidhāyeyyuṃ vasaṃ "
"gaccheyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"When those six animals became exhausted and worn out, the strongest of them "
"would get their way, and they’d all have to submit to their control."

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.12"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno kāyagatāsati abhāvitā "
"abahulīkatā, taṃ cakkhu āviñchati manāpiyesu rūpesu, amanāpiyā rūpā paṭikūlā "
"honti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a mendicant has not developed or cultivated "
"mindfulness of the body, their eye pulls towards pleasant sights, but is put "
"off by unpleasant sights. Their ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.13"
msgid "mano āviñchati manāpiyesu dhammesu, amanāpiyā dhammā paṭikūlā honti."
msgstr ""
"mind pulls towards pleasant thoughts, but is put off by unpleasant thoughts."

msgctxt "sn35.247:3.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, asaṃvaro hoti."
msgstr "This is how someone is unrestrained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.200"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.247:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, saṃvaro hoti?"
msgstr "And how is someone restrained?"

msgctxt "sn35.247:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe nādhimuccati, "
"appiyarūpe rūpe na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati "
"appamāṇacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with their eyes. If it’s pleasant they don’"
"t hold on to it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live "
"with mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.247:4.3"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, yatthassa te uppannā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where "
"those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over."

msgctxt "sn35.247:4.4"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "They hear a sound … smell an odor … taste a flavor … feel a touch …"

msgctxt "sn35.247:4.5"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme nādhimuccati, appiyarūpe dhamme na "
"byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati appamāṇacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"know a thought with their mind. If it’s pleasant they don’t hold on to it, "
"and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of "
"the body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.247:4.6"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te uppannā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where "
"those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.247:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso chappāṇake gahetvā nānāvisaye nānāgocare "
"daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to catch six animals, with diverse territories and "
"feeding grounds, and tie them up with a strong rope."

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.2"
msgid "Ahiṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "They’d catch a snake,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.3"
msgid "Susumāraṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "a crocodile,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.4"
msgid "Pakkhiṃ gahetvā … pe …"
msgstr "a bird,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.5"
msgid "kukkuraṃ gahetvā …"
msgstr "a dog,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.6"
msgid "siṅgālaṃ gahetvā …"
msgstr "a jackal,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.7"
msgid "makkaṭaṃ gahetvā daḷhāya rajjuyā bandheyya."
msgstr "and a monkey,"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.8"
msgid "Daḷhāya rajjuyā bandhitvā daḷhe khīle vā thambhe vā upanibandheyya."
msgstr ""
"tie each up with a strong rope, then tether them to a strong post or pillar."

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te, bhikkhave, chappāṇakā nānāvisayā nānāgocarā sakaṃ sakaṃ "
"gocaravisayaṃ āviñcheyyuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Then those six animals with diverse domains and territories would each pull "
"towards their own domain and territory."

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.10"
msgid ""
"ahi āviñcheyya ‘vammikaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti, susumāro āviñcheyya ‘udakaṃ "
"pavekkhāmī’ti, pakkhī āviñcheyya ‘ākāsaṃ ḍessāmī’ti, kukkuro āviñcheyya ‘"
"gāmaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti, siṅgālo āviñcheyya ‘sīvathikaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti, makkaṭo "
"āviñcheyya ‘vanaṃ pavekkhāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"The snake would pull one way, thinking ‘I’m going into an anthill!’ The "
"crocodile would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the water!’ The "
"bird would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m flying into the sky!’ The dog "
"would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the village!’ The jackal "
"would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the charnel ground!’ The "
"monkey would pull another way, thinking ‘I’m going into the jungle!’"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.11"
msgid ""
"Yadā kho te, bhikkhave, chappāṇakā jhattā assu kilantā, atha tameva khīlaṃ "
"vā thambhaṃ vā upatiṭṭheyyuṃ, upanisīdeyyuṃ, upanipajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"When those six animals became exhausted and worn out, they’d stand or sit or "
"lie down right by that post or pillar."

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.12"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno kāyagatāsati bhāvitā "
"bahulīkatā, taṃ cakkhu nāviñchati manāpiyesu rūpesu, amanāpiyā rūpā "
"nappaṭikūlā honti … pe … jivhā nāviñchati manāpiyesu rasesu … pe …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a mendicant has developed and cultivated mindfulness "
"of the body, their eye doesn’t pull towards pleasant sights, and isn’t put "
"off by unpleasant sights. Their ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.13"
msgid ""
"mano nāviñchati manāpiyesu dhammesu, amanāpiyā dhammā nappaṭikūlā honti."
msgstr ""
"mind doesn’t pull towards pleasant thoughts, and isn’t put off by unpleasant "
"thoughts."

msgctxt "sn35.247:5.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, saṃvaro hoti."
msgstr "This is how someone is restrained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.247:6.1"
msgid ""
"‘Daḷhe khīle vā thambhe vā’ti kho, bhikkhave, kāyagatāya satiyā etaṃ "
"adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘A strong post or pillar’ is a term for mindfulness of the body."

msgctxt "sn35.247:6.2"
msgid "Tasmātiha vo, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "sn35.247:6.3"
msgid ""
"‘kāyagatā no sati bhāvitā bhavissati bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā "
"anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will develop mindfulness of the body. We’ll cultivate it, make it our "
"vehicle and our basis, keep it up, consolidate it, and properly implement "
"it.’"

msgctxt "sn35.247:6.4"
msgid "Evañhi kho, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.247:6.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
